    slug: "history-of-islam-3-vol",
    description: `History of Islam (3 Volume Set) is a comprehensive English-language historical work that presents the full sweep of Islamic history from the time of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) through the major eras and civilizations that have defined the Muslim world over the past fourteen centuries. Published across three substantial volumes, this work provides one of the most thorough and accessible accounts of Islamic civilization available in the English language, making it an essential reference for students, educators, researchers, and general readers who want to understand the historical development of Islam and its impact on world history. The three-volume format allows the author to devote sufficient space and attention to each major period without sacrificing depth for the sake of brevity.

The first volume covers the foundational period of Islam, beginning with the life of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) in Makkah, the migration to Madinah, the establishment of the first Islamic state, and the major battles and treaties of the Prophetic era. It continues with the era of the Rightly Guided Caliphs (Abu Bakr, Umar, Uthman, and Ali, may Allah be pleased with them all), covering the rapid expansion of the Islamic state, the internal challenges and conflicts, and the establishment of the administrative and legal foundations of Islamic governance. The volume concludes with the end of the Rashidun period and the beginning of the Umayyad Caliphate.

The second volume covers the Umayyad and Abbasid periods, which represent the classical age of Islamic civilization. The Umayyad section covers the consolidation of Islamic rule from Spain to Central Asia, the development of Islamic architecture, the translation movement, and the social and political developments of the period. The Abbasid section covers the golden age of Islamic science, philosophy, literature, and art, including the contributions of Muslim scholars in fields such as mathematics, astronomy, medicine, chemistry, and optics. The volume also addresses the political fragmentation of the Abbasid Caliphate, the rise of independent dynasties such as the Fatimids, the Seljuks, and the Ghaznavids, and the development of the major schools of Islamic jurisprudence and theology.

The third volume covers the later periods of Islamic history, including the Crusades, the Mongol invasions, the rise of the Ottoman, Safavid, and Mughal empires, the period of European colonialism and its impact on the Muslim world, and the emergence of modern nation-states in the Islamic world. The volume addresses the intellectual and reform movements that arose in response to the challenges of modernity, including the Wahhabi, Sanusi, and Mahdi movements, and the contributions of modern Muslim thinkers and reformers. Throughout all three volumes, the author maintains a balanced and scholarly approach, drawing upon both Muslim and non-Muslim sources, and presenting the history in a manner that is informative, engaging, and respectful of the Islamic tradition. The set is an invaluable resource for anyone seeking a comprehensive understanding of Islamic history from its origins to the present day.`,
    metaDescription: "History of Islam 3-volume set covers Islamic civilization from the Prophet to modern era in English. Comprehensive reference for students."
